.TH EWFTS 1 "2026-05-04" "1.0" "EWFTS Manual"

.SH NAME
ewfts \- Ephemeral Wrapper for Temporary Scripts
.br
.SH SYNOPSIS
ewfts [-file <path>] <command> [args...]
.br
.SH DESCRIPTION
EWFTS executes a command and associates it with a single file that is
treated as temporary. After execution completes, the selected file is
automatically deleted.
.br
.SH FILE HANDLING MODEL
EWFTS selects a file using the following rules:
.br
1. If -file <path> is provided, that file is used.
.br
2. Otherwise, the last positional argument is treated as the file.
.br
Before execution, EWFTS rewrites the command so that the file is always
.br
passed as the final argument to the executed process.
.br
The file is deleted after execution completes.
.br
.SH EXAMPLES
ewfts cat file.txt
.br
ewfts -file file.txt cat
.br
ewfts echo hello world file.txt
.br
.SH EXIT STATUS
0   Success
.br
1   Error (invalid arguments, missing file, or execution failure)
.br
.SH SEE ALSO
bash(1), python3(1)
.br
